{Speech 16}{}{Time:60000 No answer:Close dialog / Close dialog}
{Speech 16 Answer 6}{}{As they say, sportloto is your Game!}
{Speech 16 Answer 32}{}{Tell me about this sportloto.}
{Speech 16 Answer 30}{}{And what's this Jet?}
{Speech 16 Answer Exit}{}{All right, good to know. Bye.}
{Speech 17}{}{Time:60000 No answer:Close dialog}
{Speech 17 Answer 18}{}{An apple?}
{Speech 17 Answer Exit}{}{Not now, sorry. Bye.}
{Speech 18}{}{I love apples a lot, but there are none here at all. They bring 'em in once in a blue moon.}
{Speech 18 Answer 19}{}{I heard an apple gives such a great kick because it's eaten really slowly.}
{Speech 19}{}{Eaten slowly? You're a real dumpling, completely lost it! Apples get eaten just as fast as any other fruit. If the traders didn't act up, we'd all be stuffing ourselves with fruit here.}
{Speech 19 Answer 23}{}{You're talking nonsense, I think. You've boozed up on your denatured spirit - that's why you're tripping.}
{Speech 19 Answer 49}{}{ Tell me about something else instead.}
{Speech 19 Answer Exit}{}{Yeah, sure, apples are super. (slowly stepping back) Of course, Vuz, everything's gonna be fine, calm down. Goodbye.}
{Speech 20}{}{Well, I think we understood each other. Anything else?}
{Speech 20 Answer 49}{}{Yes, I'd like to find out something else. }
{Speech 20 Answer 49*}{}{I think we should wrap up the trade here. I've got a couple more questions...}
{Speech 20 Answer Exit}{}{I don't need anything else for now.}
{Speech 21}{}{Oh, the Chosen One. Damn, didn't recognize you. Come here, I'll tell you something in your ear.}
{Speech 21 Answer 24}{}{Now that's more like it. After all, I do deserve at least a little respect.}
{Speech 21 Answer Exit}{}{No way, I won't even come near you, you stinking corpse. Forget it. Bye.}
{Speech 23}{}{Come here, I'll tell you in your ear.}
{Speech 23 Answer 24}{}{Okay.}
{Speech 23 Answer Exit}{}{No way! You wanna eat my brains, you sneak. That's it, I'm gone. Bye.}
{Speech 24}{}{Time:60000 No answer:Close dialog}
{Speech 24 Answer Exit}{}{Wasn't that keen on sitting in your damn bar anyway. You didn't have to yell so loud.}
{Speech 24 Answer Exit*}{}{Well then, you freak, you've had it coming. Time to teach you a lesson, you freak.}
{Speech 25}{}{Time:60000 No answer:Close dialog}
{Speech 25 Answer 49}{}{All right, Mister Vuz, sorry for bugging you so much. I just wanted to ask you a couple of questions.}
{Speech 25 Answer Exit}{}{You're telling ME to go to @#%? Why don't you take a walk yourself? Your bar is shit, got it? That's it, I'm leaving. }
{Speech 25 Answer Exit*}{}{All right, forget it, Vuz. Sorry.}
{Speech 25 Answer 26}{}{Did I tell you how much I love apples?}
{Speech 26}{}{Really? I didn't know. Well, if you love apples, maybe you're not as much of a piece of crap as you seem. So what the hell do you want?}
{Speech 26 Answer 49}{}{I wanted to ask you a few questions, Vuz.}
{Speech 27}{}{Time:60000 No answer:Close dialog}
{Speech 27 Answer 28}{}{What?}
{Speech 28}{}{Time:60000 No answer:Close dialog}
{Speech 28 Answer Exit}{}{Deaders, zombies, what's the difference? Either way you're freaks...}
{Speech 29}{}{Cards aren't just a game - they're a passion. They even change people's lives and fates, often leading them to a tragic end they don't even suspect.}
{Speech 29 Answer 31}{}{Uh-huh...}
{Speech 30}{}{Time:60000 No answer:Close dialog}
{Speech 30 Answer 32}{}{A-a-ah, oh right, Jet, of course. Tell me more about the cards.}
{Speech 31}{}{Time:60000 No answer:Close dialog}
{Speech 31 Answer Exit}{}{Some other time... [Exit.]}
{Speech 32}{}{Time:60000 No answer:Close dialog}
{Speech 32 Answer 29}{}{Yeah, got it. And you also can't trade cards with other players except on Thursday evening? Stupid, of course, but you can play.}
{Speech 32 Answer Exit}{}{I'd rather play later. Thanks for teaching me at least.}
{Speech 33}{}{The bar's named the Harp after a hangout where I used to hang around before the war. Sort of a reminder of the past and a symbol of hope for rebirth.}
{Speech 33 Answer 35}{}{Before the war? But that was ages ago.}
{Speech 33 Answer 37}{}{Hope for rebirth? What do you mean by that?}
{Speech 34}{}{Maybe, but not everyone lives in cities full of bloodthirsty lunatics.}
{Speech 34 Answer 36}{}{What do you mean?}
{Speech 35}{}{Of course it was long ago. And where do you think the ghouls came from? What, you think someone just got up one morning and said to himself: Holy crap, why don't I become a living corpse with rotting flesh?}
{Speech 35 Answer 38}{}{Well, no, I didn't think so. So where did the ghouls really come from?}
{Speech 35 Answer 25}{}{You know, I really couldn't give a damn why you ghouls turned into such freaks.}
{Speech 36}{}{Time:60000 No answer:Close dialog}
{Speech 36 Answer 27}{}{Thanks for the advice, I'll be more careful. Can I ask you something else?}
{Speech 36 Answer Exit}{}{And I think they found the right way - a genetic cleansing wouldn't hurt our society, and they should've started with you. Bye.}
{Speech 36 Answer Exit*}{}{Wasting you freaks... Bye}
{Speech 37}{}{With attitudes like that in society, the ghouls won't get any relative peace and independence for a long while, and for now the harp will be our symbol and our hope.}
{Speech 37 Answer 37}{}{I'd never have thought ghouls were so musical.}
{Speech 37 Answer 49}{}{Yeah, I see. Heh-heh-heh. Can I ask something?}
{Speech 38}{}{Well, it wasn't the good Lord who made us this way, you dummy! War... and radiation. What, never heard of it? When the bombs went off, the nuclear flame burned our flesh, and the radiation, the kind that doesn't kill but just destroys you cell by cell, finished the job.}
{Speech 38 Answer 39}{}{Yeah. I see.}
{Speech 39}{}{Finally. And anyway, why the hell did you have to stir up all these already painful memories? You bastard, we're just a pile of rotting garbage, slightly overcooked rotting garbage.}
{Speech 39 Answer 49}{}{I'd say undercooked... Ahem, all right, never mind. Let me ask you something else.}
{Speech 39 Answer Exit}{}{All right, I won't keep you from feeling sorry for yourself. Bye.}
{Speech 40}{}{Time:60000 No answer:Close dialog}
{Speech 40 Answer 41}{}{Bastards?}
{Speech 41}{}{Time:60000 No answer:Close dialog}
{Speech 41 Answer 49}{}{Off an oak? Don't recall that... Can I ask you another question?}
{Speech 42}{}{Time:60000 No answer:Close dialog}
{Speech 42 Answer 43}{}{Okay, a torn-off head. So what's the point?}
{Speech 42 Answer 43*}{}{Heh... well?}
{Speech 43}{}{Time:60000 No answer:Close dialog / Close dialog}
{Speech 43 Answer 44}{}{Wait, wait. A torn-off head flying around Hell? And what's it doing there?}
{Speech 43 Answer 44*}{}{Heh-heh-heh-heh... oooh... }
{Speech 44}{}{Time:60000 No answer:Close dialog / Close dialog}
{Speech 44 Answer 45}{}{What are you, some kind of pervert? Were you a bit too tender with your mother? Did you wet the bed?}
{Speech 44 Answer 47}{}{Aha-ha-ha-ha! [shaking]. You're something, Vuz!}
{Speech 45}{}{No no no, hold on. The whole point is in the head. Get it? Just picture a torn-off head in Hell, it's hilarious! How can you not laugh imagining a torn-off head in Hell?}
{Speech 45 Answer 46}{}{Vuz, I don't know you well, of course, but I think I'll be right if I say you need medical help. Immediate, qualified medical help. }
{Speech 45 Answer 47}{}{Ah, oh right, of course, that's very funny. Ha-ha-ha, of course. So funny I can barely eat. Ahem, well all right, we've had our laugh, that's enough. I've got a couple more questions for you.}
{Speech 46}{}{Time:60000 No answer:Close dialog / Close dialog}
{Speech 46 Answer 49}{}{I guess you're right, Vuz. I really am not as smart as you. You're the one bright mind among us pigs. In that case, answer me one more question.}
{Speech 47}{}{Well! Told you it was a killer joke.}
{Speech 47 Answer 49}{}{ }
{Speech 49}{}{Ask away}
{Speech 49 Answer 12}{}{Booze, Vuz}
{Speech 49 Answer 5}{}{What are you doing here?}
{Speech 49 Answer 10}{}{Tell me about this place.}
{Speech 49 Answer Exit}{}{I don't need anything from you. Bye.}
